cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.DC

This paper is about optimizing the back-end design of digital circuits using machine learning. The topic is related to electronic design automation (EDA) and optimization, which falls under the category of cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). The paper also discusses the use of heuristic algorithms and the development of a framework to improve the performance and quality of the design, which could be categorized under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of machine learning to optimize the design process also involves system-level considerations, which could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the use of perturbed training samples, which could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
